@startuml
title Library Borrowing Management System V2 - Simplified Architecture

skinparam componentStyle rectangle

package "com.library" {
  [Main] --> [ConsoleMenu]
}

package "com.library.ui" {
  [ConsoleMenu]
}

package "com.library.service" {
  [LibraryService]
}

package "com.library.database" {
  [LibraryRepository]
  [DatabaseConnection]
}

package "com.library.model" {
  [Model Classes]
}

package "support packages" {
  [enums]
  [exceptions]
}

database "MySQL/MariaDB\nlibrary_db" as DB

[ConsoleMenu] --> [LibraryService] : calls workflows
[LibraryService] --> [LibraryRepository] : applies rules, asks for data
[LibraryRepository] --> [DatabaseConnection] : obtains JDBC Connection
[DatabaseConnection] --> DB : JDBC
[LibraryService] ..> [Model Classes] : uses objects
[LibraryRepository] ..> [Model Classes] : maps SQL rows
[LibraryService] ..> [enums]
[LibraryService] ..> [exceptions]
[LibraryRepository] ..> [enums]

note right of [ConsoleMenu]
Official V2 demo is console-based.
No Swing core.
end note

note bottom of [LibraryService]
Business rules:
loan limit, unpaid fines,
copy availability, reservation rules.
end note

note bottom of [LibraryRepository]
Simple SQL repository.
No many-DAO architecture in V2.
end note
@enduml
